# 🚀 C++ Projects Collection

Welcome to the **Projects-C++** directory! This folder contains C++ projects developed as part of my learning journey. Each project is designed to strengthen programming concepts, improve problem-solving skills, and provide hands-on experience with real-world applications.

## 📖 About

The projects in this directory range from beginner to intermediate level and demonstrate practical implementations of C++ concepts, including object-oriented programming, file handling, data structures, and the Standard Template Library (STL).

## ✨ Features

* Clean and well-structured C++ code
* Console-based applications
* Object-Oriented Programming (OOP)
* STL usage
* File handling
* Beginner-friendly implementations
* Easy to understand and modify

## 📂 Project List

This folder may include projects such as:

* 🎮 Console Games
* 🧮 Calculator
* 🏦 Bank Management System
* 📚 Library Management System
* 👨‍🎓 Student Management System
* 📝 To-Do List
* 📂 File Management Utilities
* 🔢 Number & Pattern Programs
* 🎯 Other practice projects

> New projects will be added as I continue learning and exploring C++.

## 🛠️ Requirements

* C++ Compiler (GCC/G++)
* Visual Studio Code, Code::Blocks, Dev-C++, or any C++ IDE

## ▶️ Compile & Run

Compile a project:

```bash
g++ project.cpp -o project
```

Run the executable:

**Windows**

```bash
project.exe
```

**Linux / macOS**

```bash
./project
```

